I would definitely place Sommore as one of the top black comedians of our time, and I am white. Her delivery was fantastic. Now, although crude and a lot of explicit language, behind all that the audience can see a well-rounded, powerful, and intelligent woman. Many comedians today have crudeness and explicit language in their acts, but show not an ounce of intelligence, and their need to be obnoxious and rude overpowers what could have been a good act. Not with Sommore! She has the striking ability to remain classy and intelligent and still put people in their place.

Best standup I've ever seen...and I've seen a lot!  Sommore is #1 in standup.  Period.  She is the best American comic working today (Aziz Ansari is a close second).  Every second of this DVD is comedy gold.  The jokes are awesome, over and over, you will wear out the DVD and still be laughing over the jokes years later.  She's brought some brilliant satire here.  Best standup since Eddie Murphy's "Raw."
